  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Article/2034080">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Article"/>
    <so:title>Geometric forms in landscape – lighthouses</so:title>
    <so:article_ID>oai:bibliotekanauki.pl:2034080</so:article_ID>
    <so:abstract>The subject of this study is the potential of lighthouses located in the West Pomeranian Voivodeship as a leitmotif for the EuroVelo 10 bicycle trail. The study examined from which places on the trail lighthouses can be seen, marked places where panoramic views of the sea open, and suggested activities that could help improve the exposure of lighthouses from the perspective of the trail. It was found that 6 of the 7 surveyed objects are already visible, in some form, from the trail. It was con cluded that lighthouse objects are already or could become valuable landmarks for EuroVelo 10 route, but it should be considered how to maintain continuity of visual experience on the sections between lighthouses.</so:abstract>
    <so:publication_year rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">2021</so:publication_year>
    <so:publisher>['Zachodniopomorski Uniwersytet Technologiczny w Szczecinie. Wydawnictwo Uczelniane ZUT w Szczecinie']</so:publisher>
  </rdf:Description>
